OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FDisabled woman and service 
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fdog told to leave pub      
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5F                           
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, A disabled woman said she was reduced  
OL,6, to tears when asked to leave a pub     
OL,7, because of her assistance dog.         
OL,9,FLouise Harris, who has multiple        
OL,10,Fsclerosis, was approached by a manager 
OL,11,Fin Hanley Wetherspoons on 13 January.  
OL,13,F"I was in utter shock, I could not     
OL,14,Fbelieve it," said Ms Harris, adding she
OL,15,Fhad provided proof cockapoo Bella was a
OL,16,Fservice dog.                           
OL,18,FWetherspoons said in a statement it had
OL,19,Fa "no-dog policy", but assistance dogs 
OL,20,Fwere allowed in its pubs.              
